    "assistantText": "I was only able to reliably validate **1 qualified lead** that meets all your constraints (MSP/SI, US-based, <~120 employees, has email). The pipeline had difficulty finding enough *high-confidence, size-verified* small providers specifically in **North Carolina and Ohio** while also confirming emails.\n\nHere is what I have so far, and then I’ll outline options to get you to 20 leads:\n\n---\n\n### 1) Validated Lead\n\n**Company:** Integrated IT Solutions  \n**Website:** https://www.integratedit.com/  \n**Type:** Managed IT Services / MSP  \n**Description:** Provides managed IT services, network management, cybersecurity, cloud solutions, and IT consulting primarily for small to mid-sized businesses.  \n**Location:** Greensboro, North Carolina, USA  \n**Employee count:** Not clearly stated online; public signals indicate a small firm (likely under 100 employees), but this is not definitively confirmed.  \n**Contact email(s):**  \n- `info@integratedit.com` (general inquiries)\n\n---\n\n### Why only 1 lead?\n\nThe automated lead pipeline enforces:\n\n- **Strict geo + size filters** (US, 1–120 employees)  \n- **Industry match** to MSP / IT services / systems integrator  \n- **Email required**  \n- Confidence threshold ≥ 0.6\n\nWithin those filters, it only found **one company where all criteria (especially size + email) could be reasonably validated** in the time/visit budget.\n\nMany MSPs/SIs in NC and OH either:\n- Don’t list staff size anywhere reliable, or  \n- Appear to be larger regional/national players, or  \n- Have contact forms only (no visible email address).\n\n---\n\n### How do you want to proceed?\n\nI see a few options, and I can run another pass tailored to what matters most to you:\n\n1. **Relax size verification**  \n   - Still *aim* for <100 employees but accept companies where size is unknown or estimated from LinkedIn / job pages.  \n   - This will yield more leads, but size will be “best-effort,” not strictly confirmed.\n\n2. **Relax geography slightly**  \n   - Prioritize NC and OH, but allow nearby states (e.g., SC, VA, KY, IN, PA).  \n   - Might be useful if you’re selling remotely and just want a regional focus.\n\n3. **Relax the email constraint**  \n   - Include MSPs/SIs that only have contact forms, then optionally do manual enrichment or a separate email discovery step later.\n\n4. **Fewer leads, higher quality**  \n   - I can build a **short, fully verified list (e.g., 5–10)** with manual cross-checking and richer detail per company.\n\nTell me which tradeoff you prefer (e.g., “Keep NC/OH, relax size verification, keep email required, and still target 20 leads”), and I’ll rerun the search with that in mind and then present as many solid leads as I can, clearly marking where size is estimated vs confirmed."
